The paper focuses on Neural Architecture Search (NAS) for image classification tasks, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper proposes a new method for NAS that involves knowledge distillation, which is a technique commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE). The paper also discusses the use of shared network parameters, which is a topic related to distributed systems (cs.SY).
